data.title: Teaser Trailer
data.text:
You may watch below the first official trailer of Most beautiful Island, the upcoming drama thriller movie written and directed by Ana Asensio and starring Ana Asensio, Natasha Romanova, David Little, Nicholas Tucci, Larry Fessenden, Caprice Benedetti, Anna Myrha, Ami Sheth, Miriam A. Hyman, Sara Visser, Natalia Zvereva, Jennifer Sorika Wolf, and Fenella A. Chudoba:

MOST BEAUTIFUL ISLANDPlot synopsis:

“A psychological thriller examining the plight of undocumented female immigrants hoping to make a life in New York. Shot on Super 16 with an intimate, voyeuristic sensibility, Most Beautiful Island chronicles one harrowing day in the life of Luciana (Ana Asensio), a young immigrant woman struggling to make ends meet while striving to escape her past. As Luciana’s day unfolds, she is whisked, physically and emotionally, through a series of troublesome, unforeseeable extremes.”

Doesn’t sound like the day will end that well…

Anyway, there’s also a film poster, take a look below:

(Click on the poster to enlarge.)

The release date of the movie Most Beautiful Island is set to November 3, 2017 (in select theaters).

Stay tuned with us for more details.

:)

Check out the official trailer of Sniper Ultimate Kill, the upcoming action thriller movie directed by Claudio Fah and starring Billy Zane, Tom Berenger, Danay Garcia, Juan Sebastián Calero, Joe Lando, Chad Michael Collins, Juan Pablo Gamboa, Lucho Velasco, and Felipe Calero:

SNIPER ULTIMATE KILL

A land under siege. A criminal without mercy. A war beyond borders.

A game with advanced weapons.

Plot synopsis:

“Colombian drug kingpin Jesús Morales secretly pays for the services of a sniper nicknamed ‘The Devil’, capable of killing one-by-one the enemies of anyone who hires him. With no adversaries left alive, Morales grows stronger and gains control of more smuggling routes into the United States. The DEA, alarmed by this threat to the country, sends agent Kate Estrada, who has been following Morales for years, and Marine sniper Brandon Beckett to Colombia. Their mission: Kill ‘The Devil’ and bring Morales back to the US to be tried for his crimes. The agents think they have everything under control, but Morales and “The Devil” have prepared plenty of surprises to keep the mission from succeeding.”

This new bullet is a game changer: it’s the closest thing to a magic bullet, hell yeah!

There’s also a film poster, take a look below:

(Click on the poster to enlarge.)

SNIPER ULTIMATE KILL

This time, weapons change the game.

The release date of the movie Sniper Ultimate Kill is set to October 3, 2017 (on Blu-ray & Digital).

Stay tuned with us for more details.

:)

Check out the official trailer of Found Footage 3D, the upcoming horror movie written and directed by Steven DeGennaro and starring Carter Roy, Alena von Stroheim, Chris O’Brien, Tom Saporito, Scott Allen Perry, Jessica Perrin, and Scott Weinberg:

FOUND FOOTAGE 3DPlot synopsis:

“The film tells the story of a group of filmmakers who set out to make the first 3D found footage horror movie, but find themselves IN a found footage horror movie when the evil entity from their film escapes into their behind-the-scenes footage. A swift, surprising and scary commentary on the Paranormal Activity-style of horror film.”

Damn what did just happen at the end of this trailer? Mom, am scared!

There are also two film posters:

(Click on a poster to enlarge.)

FOUND FOOTAGE 3D

From the Co-Creator of The Texas Chainsaw Massacre.

The release date of the movie Found Footage 3D is set to October 26, 2017 on Shudder (in both 2D and 3D versions) .

Stay tuned with us for more details.

:)

Take a look to the first official poster of Forever My Girl, the upcoming romantic drama movie starring Alex Roe, Jessica Rothe, John Benjamin Hickey, Abby Ryder Fortson, Tyler Riggs, Peter Cambor, Gillian Vigman, Morgan Alexandria, Lauren Gros, James Rackley, Arielle Bowden, Jason Davis, Adam Drescher, Bella Lotz, and Cody Alan:

(Click on the poster to enlarge.)

FOREVER MY GIRL

Find your way back home.

Based on the best-selling novel.

Plot synopsis:

“After being gone for a decade a country star returns home to the love he left behind.”

If the girl waited for that chap I guess it just means she wasn’t satisfied with the local gene pool, lol!

Here’s the movie trailer of Forever My Girl if you haven’t seen it yet: Continue reading »

There’s a new trailer for Maya Dardel (aka A Critically Endangered Species), the upcoming drama movie written and directed by Zachary Cotler and Magdalena Zyzak and starring Lena Olin, Rosanna Arquette, Nathan Keyes, Alexander Koch, Jordan Gavaris, and Chris Voss, watch it below:

MAYA DARDELPlot synopsis:

“An internationally lauded poet/novelist announces on National Public Radio that she is going to end her life and that young male writers may compete to become executor of her estate. The man who wins will inherit her home, land, books, unpublished manuscripts, and be expected to protect and promote her posthumous reputation.”

Yep Maya Dardel, don’t hurt yourself and just enjoy life with that young hunk!

Anyway, there’s also a new poster:

(Click on the poster to enlarge.)

The release date of the movie Maya Dardel is set to October 27, 2017 in NY and LA (with additional cities to follow).

Stay tuned with us for more details.

:)

:)

A teaser poster for Gnaw, the upcoming horror movie directed by Haylar Garcia based on a script he co-wrote with Jim Brennan and Kathryn Gould and starring Penelope Mitchell, Sally Kirkland, Chris Johnson, Kyle Gass, Han Soto, Graham Emmons, Daniel Rossano, Kathryn Gould, Kristin Keating, Dan Davidson, Susan Bellone, Elisa Vasquez, Erin Graham, Nelson Goforth, T. David Rutherford, and Jaq Walker:

(Click on the poster to enlarge.)

GNAW

Plot synopsis:

“Jennifer Conrad (Penelope Mitchell) is a small-town girl starting over in the big city. Fleeing an abusive relationship, all she wants is a chance to begin again. But it is hard to start over when something is eating you while you sleep… on painful bite at a time.

When Jennifer wakes to find her grasp at a brave, new life interrupted by tiny wounds that seem to appear while she is sleeping, her waking hours begin to take a horrific turn. Soon she finds herself trapped in a chaotic spiral forged of sleep deprivation, paranoia and a paralyzing fear of the unseen, which like a pack of emotional phantoms, begin to derail her life, even forcing her to consider the unthinkable option of going back to her abusive, but somehow twistedly stable relationship.

Jennifer’s only chance is to uncover the mystery of the strange bites, a mystery that seems to spring from the vacant apartment next door and the tortured woman who once lived there.

What Jennifer finds is a horrible revelation, something that defies belief. Something that can only be stopped through the summoning of her own inner will to remain a survivor.

But can she confront her fears, restore her sanity and ultimately wage a final battle before the last, bloody bite is taken?”

And three pictures from the film:

(Click on a picture to enlarge.)

What’s gnawing at her?

The film has yet to get an official release date.

Stay tuned with us for more details about the movie Gnaw.

:)
